    "Management": {
      "text": "If you suspect, then treat! Confirming diagnosis is difficult, treatment is low risk and effective, and morbidity/mortality is high if untreated\nThiamine\n500mg IV over 30 min TID x 2 days, then 500mg IV/IM q day for 5 days, then 100mg PO q day until patient no longer at risk\nGive\nmagnesium\n; hypomagnesemic state may be resistant to thiamine administration\nTreatment can take days to weeks to work if at all (despite accurate diagnosis)\nGive thiamine BEFORE glucose in patients requiring glucose who are at risk for thiamine deficiency; glucose without thiamine can precipitate/worsen WE by driving thiamine intracellularly",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Thiamine",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Thiamine"
        },
        {
          "text": "magnesium",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Magnesium"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Admit\n<25% of patients show full recovery, 50% show partial recovery, the remainder show no response despite treatment\n[2]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
